				<li class="footnote " id="-09205_000_042"><a name="-09205_000_042">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote33-09205_000_042">33.</a>
      </span>
					<p>&ldquo;Tell Me the Stories of Jesus.&rdquo;</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-09205_000_042"><a name="-09205_000_042">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote34-09205_000_042">34.</a>
      </span>
					<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/3.17?lang=eng#16" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Mosiah 3:17</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-09205_000_042"><a name="-09205_000_042">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote35-09205_000_042">35.</a>
      </span>
					<p>Elder Dallin&nbsp;H. Oaks once commented: &ldquo;When I was a boy, I spent most of my evenings reading books. One of my favorites was <span class="emphasis">Hurlbut&rsquo;s Story of the Bible</span>&nbsp;&hellip;&nbsp;, [a] book [of] 168 stories from the Bible. I loved these stories and read them many times&rdquo; (&ldquo;Bible Stories and Personal Protection,&rdquo; <span class="emphasis">Ensign,</span> Nov. 1992, 37).</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-09205_000_042"><a name="-09205_000_042">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote36-09205_000_042">36.</a>
      </span>
					<p>Stella Oaks, &ldquo;Thy Will Be Done,&rdquo; in Leon&nbsp;R. Hartshorn, comp., <span class="emphasis">Remarkable Stories from the Lives of Latter-day Saint Women,</span> 2 vols. (1973&ndash;75), 2:184.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-09205_000_042"><a name="-09205_000_042">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote37-09205_000_042">37.</a>
      </span>
					<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/36.17-18?lang=eng#16" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 36:17&ndash;18</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-09205_000_042"><a name="-09205_000_042">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote38-09205_000_042">38.</a>
      </span>
					<p>In our world today we need more than ever Enos&rsquo;s words about his father to be our children&rsquo;s words about us: &ldquo;The words which I had often heard my father speak concerning eternal life &hellip; sunk deep into my heart. And my soul hungered; and I [knelt] down before my Maker&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/enos/1.3-4?lang=eng#2" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Enos 1:3&ndash;4</a>).</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-09205_000_042"><a name="-09205_000_042">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote39-09205_000_042">39.</a>
      </span>
					<p>President Monson promised the youth: &ldquo;When firmly planted, your testimony of the gospel, of the Savior, and of our Heavenly Father will influence all that you do throughout your life. &hellip; Your testimony, when constantly nourished, will keep you safe&rdquo; (<span class="emphasis">Liahona</span> and <span class="emphasis">Ensign,</span> May 2009, 126).</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-09205_000_042"><a name="-09205_000_042">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote40-09205_000_042">40.</a>
      </span>
					<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/hel/5.12?lang=eng#11" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Helaman 5:12</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-09205_000_042"><a name="-09205_000_042">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote41-09205_000_042">41.</a>
      </span>
					<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/16.8?lang=eng#7" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Mosiah 16:8</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-09205_000_042"><a name="-09205_000_042">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote42-09205_000_042">42.</a>
      </span>
					<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/21.5?lang=eng#4" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Doctrine and Covenants 21:5</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-09205_000_042"><a name="-09205_000_042">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote43-09205_000_042">43.</a>
      </span>
					<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/26.12?lang=eng#11" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 26:12</a>.</p>
				</li>
			</ol>
                                        
